27 3. Liability. The liability of the center is governed by the Maine Tort Claims Act. A
28 member of the board or an employee of the center is not subject to any personal liability
29 for having acted in the service of the member's or employee's duty as a member of the board
30 or an employee of the center within the course and scope of membership or employment to
31 carry out a power or duty under this chapter. The center shall indemnify a member of the
32 board or an employee of the center against expenses actually and necessarily incurred in
33 connection with the defense of an action or proceeding in which a member of the board or
34 an employee of the center is made a party by reason of past or present association with the
35 center.
36 4. Expenses. A member of the board is not entitled to receive compensation for
37 services to the center but is entitled to receive reimbursement for necessary expenditures,
38 including travel expenses incurred in carrying out those services.
39 §13404. Maine Blue Economy Fund
40 1. Maine Blue Economy Fund established. There is established a nonlapsing fund
41 to be known as the Maine Blue Economy Fund for the purpose of receiving funds from the
42 State and gifts, grants, devises, bequests, trusts or security documents to support the
