413 operations and initiatives of the center. The State shall credit to the fund any appropriation
424 or allocation made to the center in the fiscal year in which the appropriation or allocation
435 is made.
4 A. The fund must be used to:
5 (1) Make qualified investments, grants and loans and provide incentives to eligible
6 recipients to advance the blue economy sector in the State;
7 (2) Provide business supports for new or expanding businesses;
8 (3) Purchase, lease, acquire, own, improve, use, sell, convey, transfer or otherwise
9 deal in and with a center property, a center project or any interest in a center
10 property or center project, whether tangible or intangible, as otherwise authorized
11 under this chapter;
12 (4) Pay the costs of operating, maintaining, improving and repairing all property
13 and projects of the center;
14 (5) Pay the costs of administering and operating the center, including, but not
15 limited to, all wages, salaries, benefits and other expenses authorized by the board
16 or the executive director;
17 (6) Pay the principal and premium, if any, and the interest on the outstanding bonds
18 of the center related to a center property or center project as they become due and
19 payable;
20 (7) Create and maintain reserves required or provided for in any law authorizing
21 or any security document securing the bonds of the center related to a center
22 property or center project;
23 (8) Create and maintain a capital improvement fund for a center property or center
24 project established by the board;
25 (9) Make payments in lieu of taxes and pay service fees as determined appropriate
26 by the board; and
27 (10) Pay all expenses incident to the management and operation of the center.
28 B. Any amount remaining in the fund at the close of any fiscal year is carried over and
29 credited to the fund for the succeeding year.
30 C. Money in the fund must be paid to the center on manifests approved by the Governor
31 and Legislature in the same manner as other state claims are paid.
32 D. The revenues received by and due to the center from all sources other than state
33 appropriation must be retained by the center and must be used in such a manner as the
34 board determines consistent with the provisions of this section or as otherwise provided
35 by law or by the terms and conditions of any gift, grant, devise, bequest, trust or
36 security document.
37 2. Eligible recipients. Certified blue economy businesses, research institutions and
38 educational institutions are eligible to receive funding from the center upon a majority vote
39 of the board. The board may use a competitive process to award funds.
