1 1. Acquisition of interest. A public official, member of the board or employee of the
2 center may not acquire or hold a direct or an indirect financial or personal interest in:
3 A. A center activity;
4 B. Center property; or
5 C. A contract or proposed contract in connection with a center activity.
6 2. Present or past interest in property. If a public official, member of the board or
7 employee of the center owns or controls, or owned or controlled within the preceding 2
8 years, a direct or an indirect interest in property known to be included or planned to be
9 included in a center activity, that public official, member or employee shall disclose this
10 fact immediately in writing to the board and the disclosure must be entered in the board's
11 minutes.
12 3. Recusal. A public official, member of the board or employee of the center with an
13 interest in property under this section may not participate in an action by the center
14 affecting that property.
15 4. Institutional affiliations, disclosure and recusal. Notwithstanding subsection 1,
16 an educational institution, research institution or nonprofit organization represented on the
17 board may apply for and receive funding or support from the center if:
18 A. The board member affiliated with the applicant institution or organization discloses
19 the affiliation in writing to the board prior to any deliberation, decision or vote
20 regarding the application;
21 B. The affiliated board member recuses that member from any participation in the
22 discussion, deliberation and decision on the matter; and
23 C. Action on the application is taken by a vote of a majority of the disinterested board
24 members present and voting.
25 5. Violation. A violation of this section is a Class E crime.
26 §13406. Exemption from execution
27 1. Property exempt from execution. The real and personal property, including funds,
28 of the center is exempt from levy and sale by virtue of an execution. An execution or other
29 judicial process may not be issued against the center's real and personal property, and a
30 judgment against the center may not be a charge or lien upon its real and personal property.
31 2. Construction; limitation of application. This section does not:
32 A. Prohibit the center from making payments in lieu of taxes to a municipality; or
33 B. Apply to or limit the right of an obligee to foreclose or otherwise enforce a mortgage
34 of the center or to pursue remedies for the enforcement of a pledge or lien given by the
35 center on its rents, fees, grants, revenues or other sources pledged by the center to the
36 payment of its bonds.
