5 §13408. Annual report; legislation
6 1. Annual financial report. The center shall submit annually to the Governor, the
7 Executive Director of the Legislative Council and the joint standing committee of the
8 Legislature having jurisdiction over economic development matters, no later than 120 days
9 after the close of the center's fiscal year, a complete report on the activities of the center.
10 The report may also be provided to any other member of the Legislature and to any other
11 person. The report must include all of the following for that fiscal year:
12 A. A description of the center's operations;
13 B. The center's current strategic plan for growth in the blue economy sector pursuant
14 to section 13402, subsection 7 and progress toward meeting the goals of the plan;
15 C. An accounting of the center's receipts and expenditures, assets and liabilities at the
16 end of the fiscal year;
17 D. A listing of all investments, grants, loans and incentives provided by the center
18 during the fiscal year;
19 E. A listing of all property transactions conducted during the fiscal year;
20 F. A listing of any bonds issued during the fiscal year;
21 G. A statement of the center's proposed and projected activities for the ensuing fiscal
22 year; and
23 H. Recommendations regarding further actions that may be suitable for achieving the
24 purposes of this chapter.
25 2. Legislation. After reviewing the report under subsection 1, the joint standing
26 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over economic development matters may
27 report out legislation relating to the report.
28 Sec. 2. Maine Blue Economy Center; interim report. The Maine Blue
